      • performReindexingPass

        @Scheduled(fixedDelay=60000L)
public void performReindexingPass()
        This method is called once per minute to perform any required re-indexing. During most passes this will just check and find that there are no resources requiring re-indexing. In that case the method just returns immediately. If the search finds that some resources require reindexing, the system will do multiple reindexing passes and then return.
        Specified by:
        performReindexingPass in interface IFhirResourceDaoSearchParameter<SearchParameter>

      • validateResourceForStorage

        protected void validateResourceForStorage(SearchParameter theResource,
                                          ResourceTable theEntityToSave)
        Description copied from class: BaseHapiFhirDao
        This method is invoked immediately before storing a new resource, or an update to an existing resource to allow the DAO to ensure that it is valid for persistence. By default, checks for the "subsetted" tag and rejects resources which have it. Subclasses should call the superclass implementation to preserve this check.
